Bootstrap: localimage
From: ./ubuntu_22.04.sif

%post
    ## Update APT and install required tools
    apt-get update
    apt-get install -y --no-install-recommends \
        python3 \
        python3-pip \
        make

    ## Install pytest for the automated checker
    pip3 install --no-cache-dir pytest

    ## ------------------------------------------------------------------ ##
    ## Set-up initial project directory tree and raw CSV files (ONLY)     ##
    ## ------------------------------------------------------------------ ##
    PROJECT_DIR="/home/user/data_science_project"
    RAW_DIR="${PROJECT_DIR}/raw_data"

    mkdir -p "${RAW_DIR}"

    # sales_q1.csv
    cat > "${RAW_DIR}/sales_q1.csv" <<'EOF'
id,product,units
1,Widget,10
2,Gadget,
3,Thingamajig,5
EOF

    # sales_q2.csv
    cat > "${RAW_DIR}/sales_q2.csv" <<'EOF'
id,product,units
4,Widget,7
5,Gadget,3
6,Thingamajig,
EOF

    ## Ensure the student (non-root runtime user) can freely modify the tree
    chmod -R a+rwx "${PROJECT_DIR}"

%environment
    chmod 755 /home/user

    # Nothing special required; keep default HOME binding.

%labels
    Author task-setup
    Description Data-cleaning Makefile challenge – initial state only.

%help
    This container provides the starting filesystem layout for the
    data-cleaning Makefile exercise.  Only the raw_data directory and its
    CSV files exist; the student must create the Makefile and subsequent
    outputs.  Pytest is installed so the automated checker can run.